< review>
I liked this trail. It was a bit hard on the beginning, but then it became more or less flat. At the end you will be rewarded with the beautyful view of Lake Tahoe and the lakes behind the crest. Some snow patches today made the hike more enjoyable and fun :)< /review>

< Review>
Beautiful hike, but get there early if you want a good parking spot. The trail gets a little crowded in the afternoon since you come back on the same trail, but take your time exploring the creek and Cascade Falls, there are plenty of little hidden gems all around. Also bring some lunch as there are plenty of places to hang out in the shade and enjoy the views while you eat.<//Review>
<Pics>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipP9kIOuQTHacVb4eL98V-WRcCa_h8hcGHofhfdL=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPzn1Lw66VmlUWwMrBr6b8stm2aatS1tJFHgyqC=w150-h150-k-no-p']}, {'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipNl81OTtIok2LS6fBLhPPNGyLNPdf8gcWO7Z9jj=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]</Pics><Resp>None</Resp>< Gmap_id>

< Text>
Recommend for sunrise/sunset hike as it's a short 3/4mi in and another 3/4mi out. Seems heavily tracked although I've only seen three people out there for my sunset hike. My favorite part was hanging out on a rock and sitting there with some folks but definitely go to the waterfall.

About the hike, it's not strenuous. Incline is steady. GOOD FOR KIDS. Be mindful driving to the trailhead. You drive through a campsite before reaching the parking lot.<//Text>

<rating>5<//rating>< Text>
Was here and the views were amazing. The waterfall thats there doesn't actually run year round or much so it was disappointing to hike 40ish mintues to no waterfall.
However dont let that discourage you from going. Its breath taking.
What I would say though is make sure to use the restroom before driving in and to cool it on the water.
The restrooms are horrible. As in if I were to post a picture of it on here it would make you sick.
Let's just leave it at that.< /Text>

Took two kids 8 and 11 and they had a blast. Lots of boulders and rocks along the way, very fun!  This is an easy to moderate hike. Bring a snack or lunch to eat at the falls (trail ends above the falls, you see them as you hike in and out). 2 miles round trip.  Started at the trailhead 10 am done by Noon. Plenty of time left in the day to hit another site or activity. Parking is FREE but very small, go early.< /text><date>1498533638724<//date><pictures>[{'url': ['https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/p/AF1QipPu-PDvEqoH6XHQjin8Z1b_tkzSub8qJY0g8emI=w150-h150-k-no-p']}]< /pictures></record></dataset><record>

<Review>Unparalleled views. Glad I went.  Even happier that I didn't give myself a heart attack.  Seriously, this trail is no joke!   Grades are steep and consistent ALL the way up.  Desolation Trail, you'd think the name would have given me a clue!!
Anyway, I am 55 years old and sedintary.   There was a woman up there looking for her dog.  She had already gone up and down the trail, and then JOGGED back up calling for her dog.  Wow,  she was a beast!!!!  So it's all relative to your fitness level.  Take water, for sure.   I wish I had sprayed bug repellent on my arms beforehand.  Otherwise, no regrets.  We went late in the day, no trouble parking or crowds. Nice!<//Review>< pictures>
None< /pictures>

<Date>1536000389741</Date><Rate>5<//Rate><Review>We hiked from here up to Maggies Peak, then down the other side to Eagle Lake, about 4 hrs total.

Great hike, INCREDIBLE views, a good uphill challenge. We left about 9 am, and saw very few people, until our descent. I highly recommend starting at Bayview and ending at Eagle - Eagle seems to be a lot steeper ascent. We were able to easily walk back to our car at Bayview.< /Review><Pics>None</Pics>< resp>

117553802566356457361< /user_id>
< name>
Wes Lambert< /name>
<time>1450575703626<//time><Rating>3</Rating><Review>It's Open 24 Hours

This restaurant is what I have come to expect from the typical fast food restaurant.  It has food that is mostly consistent across each location.  So you know what you are getting. But the presentation and attitude of the employees is consistently disappointing.

The contrast between the employees at the Chick-fil-A down the street and this Jack-in-the-Box is a night and day. Here, the flat expression and minor disinterest in the work is a dead giveaway. And this attitude is OFTEN reflected in both the presentation of the food, the manner that it is prepared, and the taste.

I usually go through the drive-thru, and if I happen to order a Chocolate Milkshake, half of the time it will be a sloppy mess that is more liquid than shake.  The only other thing that is often done poorly is the regular french fries, which are typically burnt.

I like this restaurant because it is open 24 hours, unlike most other restaurants in the area. But if almost any other restaurant was open 24 hours, I'd probably go there instead.

Bottom Line: It's open 24 hours and it's familiar food, but the quality could use some help< /Review><Pics>None< /Pics>< response>
None<//response>

< text>
Honestly, I was so hangry I failed to take pictures. Let's start with the customer service...
Two friendly face people were working (1 female and 1 male). The place was not packed and our orders were taken right away.  We received our order number and sat down. I took my cup and was so excited that they offered sparkling lemonade in pink and lime!  Okay now the food...
I ordered a hamburger, sweet potato fries and that drink I spoke about earlier (sparkling lemonade). The burger was freshly grilled. fresh lettuce, onions (no sauce because I like knowing exactly what on my food). It was a plump burger that tasted like a burger should taste. My sweet potato fries were underwhelming. They were bright orange which made me wonder if a regular potato had been dyed orange. They tasted like regular french üçü. All in all, with the great customer service and fresh burger I would return...and order different friesüòâ</text>

< Review>
My company ordered from them for an office lunch meeting and we were less than impressed. The food was OK overall if you ordered one of their pasta dishes, but one of the salads that someone ordered was just boring and sad: tons of iceberg lettuce with some tomato, olives and grated parmesan cheese on top. Worse of all, the salad dressing container had burst in transit and it was a complete loss. A bunch of other stuff had leaked as well, so the way they package things for delivery seems inadequate. And speaking of packaging, the plastic lids on containers  for the lasagna and eggplant parmesan were so thin and flimsy that it was actually MELTED into the food--no bueno! I'd gotten the cheese ravioli, and while it wasn't offensive in any way, it was also pretty humdrum. Afterwards we all agreed that we probably won't be ordering from them again.</Review>

<Text>Shopping at Angler's Arsenal is the best experience I ever had at a bait & fishing tackle shop and quite possibly one of the best customer service experiences I ever encountered at ANY business! John Jr. and Jon the father and son combo who run Angler's Arsenal and Western Plastics (the company name for their custom plastic lures) are stand-up guys! I came in to Angler's Arsenal this weekend after having a disappointing day at one of the local lakes. I came here in search of some professional fishing guidance and some tackle suggestions. What I received from Jon was on point:* Friendly and more than willing to help answer my questions.* No short answers nor quick 'Yes' responses I've encountered at many other tackle shops.* In depth description of their custom-made plastics (Western Plastics).* Suggestions on bait that is working and how to work them.* I learned that they sell individual plastics which means you can buy onesies and twosies of 4" straight tail worms, 6" curly tail worms, 9" fat worms, 3" craw daddies, 3" flukes, 5" flukes, small frogs, large frogs, etc. etc. ¬†in several color and pattern choices! (This is great because you no longer need to purchase full packs of plastic bait and you can 'sample' various items until you find what you like and what works best at your fishing hole!).I will absolutely be coming back to Angler's Arsenal for most, if not all of my fishing gear needs! Because of my incredible experience this weekend at the shop I will be telling all my friends about how great this place is and recommend they come see John and Jon to get great tackle, excellent service and fishing tips.<//Text>< Name>

<Text>Great products. We got a small quarter pipe for my teen for Christmas. I was worried it was too small also worried about the elements since we are in Utah

<Gmap_id>0x80dcd9412480f24f:0x6d8a78689f91ac66< /Gmap_id><Text>Skate paint review. I‚Äôll start out with the shipping which took less than a week in Covid times. The product is thick and sticky. Applying it took time as I wanted to make sure I got a nice thick coat. The product gave the wood a really nice wet look, think dance floor. My first minor gripe is that per directions product is supposed to be dry in 24 hours. I live at 8000‚Äô. When the product was put on it was a typical Colorado summer day with little to no humidity and blue bird sky‚Äôs. After 28 hours the product still felt tacky. The product not only made the wood look great but skates great as well. It is fast and will slide if you‚Äôre making a hard turn. Second gripe, after two months there is noticeable fading and random spots that the product is/has flaked off. I do keep a tarp on it most times. I will also be adding another coat in the spring so hopefully that will take care of those spots. Overall though great product so far.< /Text><rate>5< /rate>< username>

<gmap_id>0x80dcd9412480f24f:0x6d8a78689f91ac66<//gmap_id>< review>
Got the roll on flat rail for Xmas from my wife. Super fun rail and the 1ft roll on section allows practice/confidence for all types of grinds until you're ready to ollie into them. Rail is very sturdy and with the correct momentum there is no movement of the rail. It is held together by 4 bolts and a insert in the middle so, unless you're slamming excessive force, it's not going to bend on you. I've already spent many hours on the rail and can say it is a lot of fun for all skill levels. A small application of wax will rejuvenate this rail and go a very long way after excessive use. Thanks OC Ramps!</review>

I had the unique challenge of receiving the shipment in the middle of a hot, dry Vegas summer, from the humid climate of Orange county, CA. After letting the materials acclimate, the assembly of the entire ramp took just a few hours over a few days due to the over 110¬∞ weather. VERY simple process. I was impressed with the engineering that went into building the transitions and supporting the ramp itself. I did have to make a few cuts to fit the flat bottom panels. The thing I am most impressed with is the Skatepaint. That stuff is seriously from another planet! So amazing. Now that it's all assembled, skating the ramp is the smoothest and most solid experience. Worth the price, hands down no questions. I'll be ordering another gallon of Skatepaint in a year or so! <username>Jake Moser< /username><Date>1606490587899</Date>< Rating>

< Review>
I purchased 2 gallons of skatepaint for my 12ft wide, 5ft tall mini ramp with birch top layer. I set up a tarp to help with leaves falling. The provided tips helped with application, which was pretty straight forward. Skate surface is awesome ! Nice smooth surface that has a great grip and feel for skating. Happy I went with skatepaint instead of other random marine products or paints. After the first all day 10 skater session - it still looks amazing. I applied skate paint with lower temperatures and had a tent which limited airflow. My drying times were a little longer than quoted, but I had 3 dry days to apply and dry and everything worked out great !!<//Review>

< Review>
- Buyer Beware - While OC Ramps does allow returns, there is a lot of hidden costs to the buyer associated with this.  After you pay the shipping and re-stocking fee you aren't left with much and would consider your purchase close to final sale.  I bought a 3' quarter pipe and within 5 days I tried to cancel the order.  The ramp had yet to be delivered, was still up in Orange County, was not yet in transit to San Diego and the freight company had yet to reach out to schedule a delivery date.  I explained to OC my situation and was told I could cancel my order but would be charged shipping and a restocking fee.  Below is what they quoted me.  All said and done I would get $26 back on a $654 purchase.  Something to consider next time you are about to hit that purchase button.

‚Ä¢	Original purchase price - $654.41
‚Ä¢	30% Restocking fee (from product cost only) - $179.70
‚Ä¢	Original ship fee - $224
‚Ä¢	Return ship fee - $224
‚Ä¢	Total refund - $26.71< /Review>

<rating>4</rating>< Review>
Purchased the 8 foot quarter pipe for my 12 year old daughter.  Customer service was responsive and helpful.  It arrived before Christmas as promised, but not without many calls from myself to the shipping company for delivery updates.  Delivery of the ramp did not go as smoothly as expected, as it was delivered by one man and it arrived on a double pallet weighing several hundred pounds.  My husband and daughter built the ramp over two days, but it could have been done in one.  A powerful, fully charged drill is a must.  Definitely requires more than one to assemble.  Followed the included instructions, so assembly was straightforward.  Also purchased two quarts of the skate paint.  Only used one full quart.  However since the weather was cold and damp, it took several days to dry.  The ramp is strong and the quality is great.  Overall, if you're looking for a skate ramp, I recommend checking out OC Ramps.<//Review>

<rating>5<//rating><text>Easy to build ramps!! Everything we expected and more!!!<//text><Pictures>None<//Pictures><Response>None</Response><gmap_id>0x80dcd9412480f24f:0x6d8a78689f91ac66< /gmap_id></record></dataset><record>
<UserId.>103330255321001485462<//UserId.><user_name>Adam Hoyle< /user_name>< date>
1533863209426< /date>
< Rate>
5< /Rate>
< Review>
I purchased an 8 foot quarter pipe from OC ramps to skate and ride BMX. The kit arrived in good condition and was packaged up neatly. Instructions were easy to follow but one tip I'd recommend is to pre-set all of the screws by hand before flipping the side boards up. This will save time. It only took me and my 7-year-old son about 4 hours to build. (This includes breaks for drill charging.) It was easy to put together and a very enjoyable bonding experience. During the assembly, I called OC Ramps to double-check on something and Tyler hopped right on the phone with me and helped me out. The ramp looks and feels great -- very stable and solid. Thanks again OC Ramps!<//Review>

<rate>5</rate><Review>I purchased an 8 foot quarter pipe from OC ramps to skate and ride BMX. The kit arrived in good condition and was packaged up neatly. Instructions were easy to follow but one tip I'd recommend is to pre-set all of the screws by hand before flipping the side boards up. This will save time. It only took me and my 7-year-old son about 4 hours to build. (This includes breaks for drill charging.) It was easy to put together and a very enjoyable bonding experience. During the assembly, I called OC Ramps to double-check on something and Tyler hopped right on the phone with me and helped me out. The ramp looks and feels great -- very stable and solid. <Time>1580278126566< /Time>< rating>
5< /rating>
< review>
We purchased 2 of the 3'2" tall 6' wide quarter pipes and set them up in our garage. We connected the 2 ramps with a layer of plywood and then a layer of hardboard to create a half pipe. We considered purchasing the garage mini-ramp, but the stock dimensions weren't a good fit for our garage and I also wanted to go 1' taller than the mini-ramp. Our kids (and I) love skating this ramp. I highly recommend this ramp and, if you have the space, installing it in your garage...it only takes up 1 parking spot in our garage, and the fact that it's indoors means it gets a ton of usage and does not require weather-proofing.< /review>

<review>I would like to share my experience and review about my roll on flat rail purchase. I first called to ask questions about the rail and the girl did not know what kind of metal it was made out of and if there was a weight capacity and whats the return period policy or if there was any kind of warranty if I had issues. There was only 2 left in stock so I asked if they would be going on sale soon or if they were going to discontinue this rail. The only thing she could answer is that the last 2 rails are grey and the new ones would be yellow and there would be no sale soon. So I bought it because grey looks more like metal than bright yellow and I wanted it in time for a Christmas gift. Well the rail arrived and the metal flat base platform is bent and I cannot bend it back straight no matter how hard I try with another person. For $360 I wanted it to be perfect and it was shipped with Saran Wrap on it so it arrived damaged. It wobbles and it slides to the side because of it. I wish it was packaged better with reinforcement to the base or in some kind of box. Now if I were to return it. It would definitely be a hassle I can't just load it into a car. The refund would less than my $360. They would deduct about $60 for their Free shipping fee, and on top of that I would have to pay the post office $100 to send it back so now i'm better off keeping it.  I wish she would have gave me the option to buy the new yellow bump rail which comes apart in 4 pieces and they actually send it in a box and did I mention its on sale for $309? The funny thing is when I got this rail it came with a brochure from OC Ramps and they list it for $269. So there is no actual free shipping and I wish she would of let me know about the yellow rail because that would of been a great idea and it probably wouldn't arrived damaged. But she's a sales person and probably doesn't even skate, just saying anything she wants to make a sale. It would of been nice to get the other rail or the option. So now I glued rubber pieces on the bottom of the rail to try stabilize it better. And I get a free T-shirt and stickers for leaving a honest review, Thank you OC RAMPS!<//review>< Pics>

<Text>I ordered two gallons of Skate Paint from OC Ramps to protect a halfpipe, two quarter pipes, and a grinding box.  The cans arrived faster than expected, but got damaged during transit.  Fortunately, there were no leaks.

<Pics>None</Pics><Resp>None</Resp><user_name>Jacques Varvel< /user_name>< rate>

<Text>I purchased two quarts of Skate Paint to coat an 8ft wide by 4ft tall quarter pipe I built for my nephews.  My calculations showed one quart would not be enough to cover the entire ramp but with the two quarts I was able to cover the entire ramp and then go over any light spots.  We live in the Pacific Northwest and get our fair share of rain, that being said it is vital to seal the ramp without comprising the integrity of skating surface.  Skate Paint did the trick!  The ramp has gotten an amazing amount of use by all of the kids (and some adults) in the neighborhood and is really holding up to all of the abuse.  The price of the Skate Paint is a good investment considering the cost which goes into building a high-end skate ramp.  I would highly recommend Skate Paint.

In addition to the Skate Paint I would recommend covering the ramp with a tarp if left outside when not in use.  We added casters to our ramp so it can be flipped up and rolled indoors for easy storage during prolonged periods of really nasty weather.  OC Ramps is great!</Text><GmapID>0x80dcd9412480f24f:0x6d8a78689f91ac66< /GmapID><Date>1427833199450<//Date><user>112590329711129593097<//user></record>

<UserId.>105644241505539589714</UserId.><name>Mike Stroven<//name><time>1550506220878< /time><rating>3< /rating><text>Ordered the 2-pack of the 4' wide quarter pipe ramps.  Definitely not impressed by the attention to detail.  lot's of 2x4s sawn right at a knot.  Took some picking and rotating to get good wood facing up.  Philips head screws suck.  Not long enough to get good bite.  We went to hardware and purchased deck screws with torx drive, and the project went much better.  Between the two kits, OC shipped 3 left-sides and one right-side, so one of our OC logos is backwards.  Seeing what it took to get the plywood to conform to the curve,  I find it hightly unlikely that 2 skate moms put one of these together!  For the exorbitant price, OC should pay more attention to detail, provide better quality fasteners, and provide a method to get the plywood to curve.  (We rigged some pipes and banding straps to pull the plywood up into the curve, and used a few of the 3" screws to hold in place so we could sink our 1-5/8 deck screws. )  Overall we give this product 3 stars.<//text>< pics>

< Text>
I ordered a 3ft. wide 1/4 pipe for my son so that he could skate inside the garage during this El Nino. The ramp arrived within a few days and I was able to assemble it in about half an hour. The materials are first class, and the directions were easy to follow. OC Ramps makes the process easy because they not only supply all the pieces for assembly, but take the most tedious and time consuming process of having to measure  the transition radius and cut the pieces for assembly.

I will be ordering an additional one so that my son can have a 6 ft. wide quarterpipe or a temporary halfpipe during rainy days.

Thank you OC Ramps!</Text>

< Review>
Tea, smoothie and acai bowl venue that is worth a visit.  Have only had their acai bowls but the tea smells amazing in the morning.  Acai bowls are well-priced and reasonably topped (seems to depend on what fruit is available at the time; strawberries, blueberries and blackberries seem to all be possible, at least in the summer).  Perfect stop on the way to/from the train station.  Shop is open by 8am, but boba is only available after 10 (means the boba is fresh and not recycled from the previous day).</Review>

< Review>
Best buck for your dollar! Averaging about $4.50 a cup of boba milk tea (24oz), very strong tea flavor and the consistency of boba was on point. Chewiness and sweetness of tapioca was perfect. Also serves juices, smoothies, yogurt, acai/pitaya bowl.</Review>

<Time>1478644078864< /Time><gmap_id>0x8085807f4b62bedd:0xe7acab8d9a8c3fb7</gmap_id><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< rating>

< review>
I'm glad I came and tried this place out. It's tucked within a side street that I wouldn't normally go down. Searching for an acai bowl place brought me here. The pitaya (dragonfruit) bowl was solid and great for the $8.25 price. The consistency of the bowl was on the watery side so if you like it thicker you could probably ask.

I noticed many people were getting the boba or coffee and chilling at the few small tables outside but don't drink caffeine myself. It smelled good though! Definitely seems like a nice place to relax and chat with a friend or colleague.<//review>

<Gmap_id>0x8085807f4b62bedd:0xe7acab8d9a8c3fb7< /Gmap_id><Review>Not impressed.

I came by on a Tuesday afternoon around 1pm. There were maybe one or two other people in the store. I ordered an herbal tea with boba. The guy at the counter asked if I meant the hibiscus tea.. I asked if there were other herbal options or just that one. He pointed to the menu and said "well, we have hibiscus tea". I said ok, then sure, that's great. He charged me for the tea and boba.

When he brought me the tea 2-3 minutes later it didn't have boba. I told him I thought I had ordered boba, and his immediate reaction was "you didn't say that". I said ok... and on my hesitation he looked at me for a few seconds, then told me he could grab some from the back if I really wanted. At that point, I felt I was being an inconvenience, so I said no and left.

The tea was alright at best, the service left a bad taste in my mouth, and I certainly didn't need to pay $4 for a cup of tea I could have brewed on my own. Needless to say, I won't be back.

UPDATE: I received a reach out from the owner, Angela, following my bad experience. She apologized and asked me to give them another shot, with a drink on the house. I returned a couple of months later and she welcomed me in, made some great recommendations, and I came away happy. It still wasn't the best tea or boba I've ever had, but it was a solid offering. Changing my rating to 3 stars.< /Review></record></dataset><record>

<Text>This location is lazy, unprofessional, and doesn‚Äôt give a care about customer service.
I had ordered a dishwasher for my ill grandmother since her dishwasher had been broken for a long time. This was on Sunday the 27th. I was able to schedule an appointment for delivery and installation for October 30th.
Well, the 30th arrived and I get a phone call from the installer, Anthony, stating that he had gone to the store and they didn‚Äôt have the dishwasher yet. Looking online, it had showed the appointment was for 8am to 12pm, when in reality, the appointment was actually set for 12pm to 4pm. Anthony said he saw that on his end too, so we could wait a little bit and he would check back with me.
I decided to call 888BESTBUY to try to find out where my order was. After a little bit of digging and calling around, I was assured by a lady over the phone that my order was on the truck and ready for delivery and installation; That the ETA was 2:30pm.
About 2pm, I get a call from Anthony that he was at the store a second time to check on where this dishwasher was. It still was not at the store. He told me that the store was supposed to have called me the night before to let me know so that we weren‚Äôt just waiting around all day for an order that was never going to arrive. I never received such a phone call. I let Anthony know that the lady over the phone told me that the delivery and installation was supposed to be in about a half hour, and that everything looked fine on her end.
I decided to call 888BESTBUY again to figure out what the heck was going on.
I got help from a wonderful lady named Sammi, who was able to dig around even more and even contacted Anthony directly as well. They together figured out that the San Jose (Plant location) made a mistake by not contacting me the night before, nor did they contact me the day of. There was absolutely no communication.
Sammi explained to me that when Anthony spoke to the manager, they said that my order was in a different city and they had to fill out a form, which was supposed to have been done the day before when they were supposed to call me anyway. So it‚Äôs just more of the whole people not doing their damn job.
Sammi said that I shouldn‚Äôt have been able to schedule delivery and installation so soon, that it was supposed to black out certain days.
The only apology I got was from Sammi, who did absolutely nothing wrong. She was actually the one that helped me reschedule for a later date for delivery and installation to make certain we will get our dishwasher.
I am extremely unhappy. I made a trip out of state to California to be here with my grandmother and get a few things done to lighten the load on her. She is very sick and all of this is going to put more stress on her. I am only here for a few days.
I don‚Äôt understand why my order isn‚Äôt here when it was supposed to be or what exactly happened in general because I never got direct answers. I‚Äôm not sure what city the dishwasher is in currently or why.
I feel like someone didn‚Äôt do their job and I‚Äôm the one paying for it.
Avoid this place at all costs.< /Text>< pictures>

Looking online, it had showed the appointment was for 8am to 12pm, when in reality, the appointment was actually set for 12pm to 4pm. Anthony said he saw that on his end too, so we could wait a little bit and he would check back with me.

<review>I've been going to this best buy for gaming headsets for the past four years. Not only do they have great gaming headsets but they have an excellent two year replacement plan for them.

Just today I returned a headset I had a warranty on and they accepted it and let me put the money of not only the headset but the protection plan towards the new headset I was going to get. It was a fast and easy process and the man helping me was very sweet.

The unfortunate part was they no longer carried the exact same model of headset I am rather fond of, but I was able to easily get help from one of the on floor associates to see if there was any of that headset around at other stores, there wasn't so I went with the next best thing that was closest to the price of the headset I'd gotten.

I highly recommend that if you are someone who goes through a lot of headsets, go to Best Buy and get their two year warranties, an extra $10 or so is worth it in the long run for the expensive headsets< /review>< rate>

<username>Margaret Odamo</username><Time>1512776760342</Time><Rate>1<//Rate>< Text>
I decided to use the best buy 18 months interest free financing to purchase about $4200 worth of appliances on november 6th. Delivery was scheduled for november 9th.
I  called back the next day to change the delivery address (forgot to say I am moving from an apartment to my new house), they said since i changed the address the delivery window was no longer available (both addresses about 2.5 miles apart) and would have to be rescheduled.

Rescheduled for the following week between 8-12pm. no one showed up, driver calls to say "oh i have 12-4". I said no, was already on my way to go empty out old apartment, so had to toss all my frozen stuff.
went to best buy, cancelled the transaction and gave them back the free google chrome.
Someone called Angie called and I agreed to get re-delivery on the 24th.
delivery went smooth, no issues. all is well, then I get an  email from best buy credit card (CITI) today and they say "you missed  the first payment on december 2nd so you are charged a late fee" I went ape nuts.

I  dont have a bill yet, how can I be late, I had even written a letter to them saying my purchase date was changed to the 24th not the 6th. they say they only go by the order date, irrespective of wether you actually receive the items.  I refused to pay the late fee, paid the balance off and closed the account.
The one star is for their staff (they were all great) and the products (love my whirlpool washer, dryer and samsung fridge, also got a dyson vaccum cleaner and iphone x).  the entire experience was tedious and stressfull, I had been thinking of making best buy my go-to place for stuff but i think ill stick with amazon.<//Text>

<rating>5</rating>< text>
Long story long I arrived on bad terms and left on good terms. After coming to the understanding that the warranty for my problem was up to the manufacturer Lenovo and not a liability of Best Buy, the Geek Squad associate Kevin politely informed me that anything that could be done to fix the problem immediately would be over his head, as the problem was with a workstation urgency was present. In steps the General Manager Kellie Adams.

She laid out what Best Buy policies are and being an understanding person I accepted that I bought a low-end computer and we got what we paid for. What she did say was that she would do whatever was in her power to make sure that I walked out that door happy.

The positive attitude of Kevin and Kellie turned me from being someone that did not plan on ever coming back to Best Buy to someone who walked out the door with a purchase of two new workstations. I have a growing company and I know where I will be going for hardware from now on.

It's easy to find the motivation to write a bad review, it takes a lot for me to find it worth my time to write a positive one. If management is reading this take notes.</text>
< Name>
Ryan Sampson<//Name>
